    in_work: 'Ra in work is the founder, the chief executive, the head of state, the patriarch of the dynasty — the figure whose seat *is* the solar disk that the whole organization orbits. Ra-energy is *kingship by radiance* — not the contested kingship of Zeus (which is held by force-of-thunderbolt) but the *inherent* kingship of the sun-that-cannot-be-not-the-sun. The shadow is the executive whose Apophis (the chaos-force inside the organization — the toxic employee, the unaddressed conflict, the unprocessed grief) has not been fought at the seventh hour, so the next dawn never comes. The other shadow: the leader whose *Akhenaten-impulse* (the imposition of a single vision destroying the polytheistic ecology of the organization) has fractured the company and will not be sustained past their tenure.',
    the_gift: 'Ra gives the recognition that *kingship is solar* — that the legitimate ruler is the one whose presence simply makes the daily order possible, who fights the chaos-serpent at the seventh hour so that the next sunrise is possible for everyone else. The gift is the willingness to take the solar seat, to be the one whose radiance the system orbits, while also accepting the daily-battle that this seat requires — Apophis returns every night, and the king who refuses to fight him will lose the morning.',
