    in_work: 'Horus in work is the founder\'s heir, the dynasty-continuer, the rightful next-in-line — the figure whose authority *inherits* rather than originates. Horus-energy is *legitimate succession*. The shadow is the heir whose Set has not yet been defeated — the next-CEO whose predecessor\'s rival is still operating in the shadows; the founder\'s child who has inherited the title but not the authority. The other shadow: the eye-of-Horus that has been *torn out and not yet restored* — the leader whose vision was damaged in the succession-fight and who is trying to lead with a blinded register, refusing the Thoth-intervention (the wisdom-counselor, the therapist, the elder-mentor) that would restore them.',
    the_gift: 'Horus gives the recognition that *the throne is inheritable*. The work of the previous generation does not die with them; the dismembered father can be reassembled, the lost throne can be reclaimed, the wounded eye can be restored. The gift is the willingness to undergo the eighty-year court case — to do the long contest that legitimate succession requires, refusing the shortcuts of either outright force (Set\'s register) or pre-emptive abdication (the Akhenaten-impulse of just creating a new religion to avoid the contest).',
    the_shadow: 'The Thelemic / Crowley appropriation (1904-) framed the entire 20th century as the "Aeon of Horus" — the avenger-son replacing the dying-father — and built a Western-occult system around this register that stripped the Egyptian funerary-political context. Aleister Crowley personally identified as "the Beast 666" prophet of the Horus-aeon; the cult lineage continues (Ordo Templi Orientis, various Thelemic groups) and is a real source of Horus-discourse in contemporary occult subcultures, which mostly miss the original Egyptian theology. The other shadow: the Eye-of-Horus has been *uniquely* commodified — appearing on the US dollar bill (where it is actually the *Eye of Providence*, a separately-evolved Renaissance Christian symbol, but is frequently conflated), in countless conspiracy-theory iconographies (Illuminati / Freemasonry / New-World-Order discourse), and as generic-mystical-pendant-jewelry stripped of the *Set-tore-it-out-and-Thoth-restored-it* mythic specificity. The third shadow: the *child-Horus-on-Isis\'s-lap* iconography was directly absorbed into the Christian Madonna-and-Child, and the Egyptian source has been systematically erased in Christian art history. The fourth shadow: the *avenger-son* register has been weaponized in modern far-right and incel discourse as a charter for vendetta-against-the-father-figure who wronged the mother — Horus\'s actual story is a *court case* refereed by the divine tribunal, won by *legal patience* and *Isis-as-advocate*, not by vigilante violence.',
